Exciting news: Jeffrey Stout will give a [series of Gifford Lectures](http://blogs.ssrc.org/tif/2017/02/01/jeffrey-stout-to-give-gifford-lectures/) this May 1-11. Entitled "Religion Unbound: Ideals and Powers from Cicero to King," the lectures will "trace the ideal [of ethical religion]'s history and explain how its defenders have defined and criticized religion." Follow the lectures (they'll stream live) on the [Gifford Lectures site](http://www.ed.ac.uk/arts-humanities-soc-sci/news-events/lectures/gifford-lectures/gifford-lectures-2016-2017/professor-jeffrey-stout).